<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 21, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 5th instant, No. 161,
                            concerning public opinion in Europe as to the result of our civil war,
                            and enclosing an interesting item from Galignani relative to the rebel
                            ram Stonewall, has been received.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pike,</hi>
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>